THE PLAYER hears a ritual within, and bursts through foliage or a barrier to enter the secluded swamp grotto. 
The Player is confronted by the unexpected: an altar with a PRISONER tied to it, about to be sacrificed. 
The BANDIT LEADER and a number of BANDIT HENCHMEN are also present on either side of the leader. 
But the altar gives it away; they are actually cultists.â€¯
The Bandit Leader steps in front of the altar, closer to the Player.

The first arrow sails out of the darkness deeper in the grotto, striking
one of the Henchmen.
An arrow hits the second henchman. They fall, dead.

In quick succession, more arrows zip from the shadows, each felling a 
Bandit, none landing on the altar. Only the leader remains. Subo leaps 
down from the shadows of the branches, landing gracefullyâ€”and 
looking like a complete badass.
The Leader roars his anger and charges closer to the Prisoner, blade brandished.

Subo strikes the Leader in the shoulder with an arrow. The Leader 
ignores the arrow sticking out of him. Subo fires again, hitting the 
Leader in the chest or other shoulder. Still the leader plods forward.

The Leader is still about to plunge his blade into the Prisoner. Subo 
fires one more arrow, piercing the Leaderâ€™s throat. The Leader sprawls 
backward onto the altar, dead.â€¯His blood flows onto the altar.
Subo frees the Prisoner from the altar.

The altar starts to bubble with mystical energy, thanks to the spilled 
blood of the leader. A malformed demon is summoned upon the altar. 
Subo puts the Prisoner behind himself. They will have to take on this 
raised demon if they hope to escape.â€¯â€¯
